\begin{align*}
\text{Sum of midpoints} &= \frac{x_2 + x_3}{2} + \frac{x_1 + x_3}{2} + \frac{x_1 + x_2}{2} \\
&= \frac{x_1}{2} + \frac{x_2}{2} + \frac{x_2}{2} + \frac{x_3}{2} + \frac{x_3}{2} + \frac{x_1}{2} \\
&= \frac{2x_1}{2} + \frac{2x_2}{2} + \frac{2x_3}{2} \\
&= x_1 + x_2 + x_3 \\
&= 10.
\end{align*}
Hence, the sum of the $x$-coordinates of the midpoints of the sides of the triangle is $10$.
